<chapter xml:id="chapter-correlating-log-messages" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0">
    <title>Correlating log messages</title>
    <indexterm>
        <primary>parsing messages</primary>
        <secondary>concepts of</secondary>
    </indexterm>
    <indexterm>
        <primary>correlating log messages</primary>
    </indexterm>
    <indexterm>
        <primary>message correlation</primary>
    </indexterm>
    <indexterm>
        <primary>grouping log messages</primary>
    </indexterm>
    <para>The &abbrev; application can correlate log messages. Alternatively, you can also correlate log messages using pattern databases. For details, see <xref linkend="patterndb-correlation"/>.</para>
    <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>To group or correlate log messages that match a set of filters, use the <parameter>grouping-by</parameter> parser. This works similarly to SQL GROUP BY statements. For details, see <xref linkend="grouping-by-parser"/>.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>You can correlate log messages identified using pattern databases. For details, see <xref linkend="patterndb-correlation"/>.</para>
        </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
